metallic /mɪˈtælɪk/

1. ADJ A metallic sound is like the sound of one piece of metal hitting another. (声音) 金属般的 

例： There was a metallic click and the gates swung open. 一声金属碰撞的咔嗒声后，大门打开了。 

2. ADJ Metallic paint or colours shine like metal. 有金属光泽的 

例： He had painted all the wood with metallic silver paint. 他把所有木料涂上了有金属光泽的银漆。 

3. ADJ Something that tastes metallic has a bitter, unpleasant taste. 金属腥味的 

例： There was a metallic taste at the back of his throat. 他喉咙深处有一股金属的腥味。 

4. ADJ Metallic means consisting entirely or partly of metal. 含金属的 

例： Even the smallest metallic object, whether a nail file or cigarette lighter, is immediately confiscated. 即便是最小的金属物品，不论是指甲锉刀还是打火机，都会立刻被没收。

